## Frequently Asked Questions

**Q: Can I use this for my startup?**  
A: Only if it's for internal development/testing. If you're building a product 
   to sell or offering services to customers, you need a commercial license.

**Q: Can I use this at my company?**  
A: For internal learning/experimentation, yes. For production systems or 
   customer-facing services, you need a commercial license.

**Q: Can I contribute to this project?**  
A: Yes! Contributions are welcome. By contributing, you agree that your 
   contributions will be licensed under this same dual license.

**Q: What if I'm not sure if my use case is commercial?**  
A: If you're unsure, please reach out on GitHub Discussions. We're happy to 
   clarify and work with you.

**Q: Can I fork this and remove the commercial license requirement?**  
A: No. The license terms apply to all derivative works. Removing the license 
   or violating its terms is copyright infringement.

